preface.congress: One Hundred Fifteenth Congress of the United States of America
preface.enrolledDateline: Begun and held at the City of Washington on Tuesday, the third day of January, two thousand and seventeen

longTitle.officialTitle: To name the Department of Veterans Affairs community-based outpatient clinic in Pago Pago, American Samoa, the Faleomavaega Eni Fa’aua’a Hunkin VA Clinic.

main.enactingFormula: Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representa­tives of the United States of America in Congress assembled,

section.heading: NAME OF DEPARTMENT OF VETERANS AFFAIRS COMMUNITY-BASED OUTPATIENT CLINIC, PAGO PAGO, AMERICAN SAMOA.
section.content: The Department of Veterans Affairs community-based outpatient clinic in Pago Pago, American Samoa, shall after the date of the enactment of this Act be known and designated as the “Faleomavaega Eni Fa’aua’a Hunkin VA Clinic”. Any reference to such community-based outpatient clinic in any law, regulation, map, document, record, or other paper of the United States shall be considered to be a reference to the Faleomavaega Eni Fa’aua’a Hunkin VA Clinic.

signature.role: Speaker of the House of Representatives.
Vice President of the United States and President of the Senate.
